# MCP Memory Plugins

- When exploring prior context, project memory, or broad code knowledge, prefer MCP memory/search plugins before falling back to raw filesystem search.
- ClaudeMEM is available as `plugin-claude-mem-mcp-search`. Follow its three-layer workflow: `search` first, then `timeline`, then `get_observations` only for filtered IDs.
- If a Superpower MCP server becomes visible in the enabled MCP list, use it for relevant memory/context tasks as well.
- Always inspect an MCP tool descriptor before calling the tool.
- If a requested plugin is not visible or callable, say so briefly and continue with available tools.
